Final Project Structure — Task Management App

Task-Management/
├── .env                       # Auth0 credentials (VITE_AUTH0_DOMAIN, VITE_AUTH0_CLIENT_ID)
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── vite.config.ts             # if using Vite
├── README.md
│
└── src/
    ├── main.css               # global styles
    ├── index.tsx              # app entry point
    ├── App.tsx                # root component
    ├── routes.tsx             # main routing file
    │
    ├── auth/
    │   └── Auth0ProviderWithNavigate.tsx   # wraps app with Auth0 and router
    │
    ├── components/
    │   ├── Navbar.tsx                      # top navigation bar with login/logout
    │   ├── TaskForm.tsx                    # add/edit form for tasks
    │   └── TaskList.tsx                    # displays all tasks on Dashboard
    │
    ├── context/
    │   └── TaskContext.tsx                 # global task state provider / defines only createContext
    │   └── TaskProvider.tsx                # defines only the provider component
    ├── hooks/
    │   ├── useLocalStorage.ts              # persistent state hook
    │   ├── useTasks.ts                     # access context and CRUD task functions
    │   └── useForm.ts                      # reusable input form handler
    │
    ├── pages/
    │   ├── Dashboard.tsx                   # main page showing TaskList
    │   ├── TaskDetails.tsx                 # shows full task info
    │   ├── CreateTask.tsx                  # page to add new tasks
    │   ├── EditTask.tsx                    # page to edit existing tasks
    │   ├── Login.tsx                       # Auth0 login landing page
    │   └── Profile.tsx                     # shows logged-in user info
    │
    ├── types/
    │   ├── task.ts                         # Task interface
    │   └── auth.ts                         # Auth user interface
    │
    └── utils/
        └── validation.ts                   # input validation logic for tasks

How These Folders Work Together

Folder	            Purpose
auth/	        Handles Auth0 authentication setup with navigation support.
components/	    Reusable UI parts (Navbar, TaskList, TaskForm).
context/	    Global app state using React Context API.
hooks/	        Custom hooks for local storage, tasks, and form management.
pages/	        Full-page views for each route (Dashboard, TaskDetails, etc.).
types/	        TypeScript type definitions to ensure strong typing and maintainability.
utils/	        Reusable helpers (e.g., form validation).
routes.tsx	    Centralized route definitions using React Router v6 and Auth0 protection.
App.tsx	        Combines everything — providers, routes, and layout.